          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the sponge, 28 to 32 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease and line a 20 x 30 cm rectangular tin. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy, about 4 minutes. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in the {{plain-flour}} and {{baking-powder}}, then stir in the dissolved {{instant-coffee}} and {{walnuts}}. Spread evenly into the tin. Bake for 28 to 32 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack to cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ice and finish",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} until smooth. Add the {{icing-sugar}} in two additions and beat well. Stir in the cooled dissolved {{instant-coffee}}. Spread the buttercream over the cooled sponge in an even layer. Press walnut halves from the remaining {{walnuts}} across the surface at regular intervals. Leave to set for 30 minutes before cutting into squares.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
